  "prompt": "What are some interesting facts about Monaco?",
  "response": "Here are some interesting facts about Monaco:\n\n1. Monaco is the second smallest independent state in the world (after Vatican City)\n\n2. It has the highest population density of any country, with over 19,000 people per square kilometer\n\n3. Monaco is a constitutional monarchy ruled by the Grimaldi family, with Prince Albert II currently reigning\n\n4. The country is known for its tax haven status, with no personal income tax for residents\n\n5. The famous Monaco Grand Prix is held annually, winding through the city's streets\n\n6. Monaco has the highest life expectancy in the world, at around 89.4 years\n\n7. Gambling is a major industry, with the Monte Carlo Casino being world-renowned\n\n8. Over 75% of Monaco's population are millionaires\n\n9. The country has no natural resources and imports most of its food and energy\n\n10. Monaco is completely surrounded by France and located on the French Riviera\n\n11. The official language is French, though Italian and English are also widely spoken\n\n12. Monaco became a member of the United Nations in 1993\n\nThese facts highlight Monaco's unique status as a small but wealthy and influential principality.",
